Vol / Page: 319
Edition:
Quote: Governor Hobson has recently given to the three Islands of New Zealand the names. New Ulster, New Munster and New Leinster; but as no reference is made in recemt communications to these appellations, which are not very euphonious, and are certainly rather perplexing, from the similarily of their terminations, it would appear they are not calculated to please the public taste
